
-> Components used for adding and executing runnables and tasks in a thread.

-> Handler is the component used to interact with the message queue of a thread.
-> MessageQueue is the component that stores all the tasks and runnables that will be running in thread.
-> Looper is the component that continues to loop around this message queue and takes out runnables one at a time and executed it in the thread.

-> Looper runs an infinite loop processing messages from the thread’s message queue.
-> Main Looper is created inside the ActivityThread.main()
-> Each thread may have exactly one Looper, accessed via Looper.myLooper()

-> Handler is associated to a looper. It stores the Looper and message queue but not the entire thread.
-> Handler Obtains a Message from pool, Sets msg.callback = runnable, Inserts it into MessageQueue (sorted by time)

-> MessageQueue Holds Message objects (not just Runnables).
-> There is 1 message queue per looper.